Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.08,0:00:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Cas Lemmens.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a designer here at Apple,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.03,0:00:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm delighted to see that so
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.70,0:00:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,many people have showed up to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.62,0:00:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about designing across
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.86,0:00:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.59,0:00:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pretty amazing view from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.08,0:00:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.56,0:00:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you could see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.15,0:00:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. At Apple, we're really
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.30,0:00:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,proud of the platforms that we
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.47,0:00:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,create.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.28,0:00:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,For every platform that we've
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.34,0:00:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,created, and for every time we
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.71,0:00:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,update a platform, we aim to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.13,0:00:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,improve your day-to-day life,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.81,0:00:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopefully create a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.68,0:00:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,meaningful relationship between
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.27,0:00:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the platform and you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.60,0:00:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And that relationship doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.73,0:00:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,have to extend to just one
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.10,0:00:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.48,0:00:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The more Apple products you use,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.17,0:01:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you rely on not just
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.38,0:01:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,single platforms, but on the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.01,0:01:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,entire ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.65,0:01:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You might start your day with a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.24,0:01:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,run on your Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.10,0:01:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At work, you might be using a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.17,0:01:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,MacBook or an iMac.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.43,0:01:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When you head home, you might
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.37,0:01:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,look up public transportation on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.84,0:01:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your phone, or use CarPlay in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.78,0:01:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.33,0:01:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're at home, you might
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.19,0:01:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,unwind watching a TV show or a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.03,0:01:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,movie on the Apple TV, and at
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.07,0:01:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of the day, you might
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.34,0:01:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,finish a book on your iPad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.22,0:01:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of the device you're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.21,0:01:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,using, you can rely on Apple's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.94,0:01:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,ecosystem to recognize you, to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.04,0:01:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,understand you, and to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.03,0:01:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Creating and contributing to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.35,0:01:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this ecosystem requires a very
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.84,0:01:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,deep understanding of every
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.09,0:01:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,single platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.85,0:01:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As a designer at Apple, that's a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.49,0:01:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,very familiar challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.55,0:01:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,For every app that Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.53,0:01:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,creates, we carefully consider
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.51,0:01:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on which platforms it should
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.55,0:01:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,live, and how it should scale
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.22,0:01:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.29,0:01:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the apps that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.24,0:01:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple creates, you might notice
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.65,0:01:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that some of them live on all of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.37,0:02:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,our platforms, like Photos, or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Music.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.53,0:02:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Others only exist on a few, like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.46,0:02:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Notes, or Mail, or TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.30,0:02:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of our services work really
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.67,0:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,well if you have more than one
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,device, like ApplePay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.84,0:02:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And, others work only if you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.99,0:02:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,have multiple devices available
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time, like FaceTime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.24,0:02:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we're going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.53,0:02:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a process that we use at Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.28,0:02:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that can help you design across
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.72,0:02:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.15,0:02:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal is to efficiently, but
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.62,0:02:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,purposefully, bring your apps to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.68,0:02:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,more platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.80,0:02:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to start with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.43,0:02:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,selecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.40,0:02:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.48,0:02:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities and the context of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.88,0:02:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,each platform, and make our
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.38,0:02:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,decision based on that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.21,0:02:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.59,0:02:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we going to adapt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.04,0:02:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to look at all the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.94,0:02:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,features and functionality we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,want to bring to our platforms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and manage that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.34,0:02:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we conform.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.92,0:02:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to find a balance between
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.18,0:02:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our own brand and the platform
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.55,0:02:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines, and to find our look
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we connect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.96,0:03:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We see what happens when you go
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.10,0:03:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from one platform to another,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.73,0:03:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it can make that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.68,0:03:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,experience seamless and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.06,0:03:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.60,0:03:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And, lastly, if possible, we try
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to extend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.73,0:03:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We see what can happen when
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.52,0:03:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple platforms become
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.74,0:03:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,available at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.91,0:03:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the entire process, and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,hopefully, at the end of this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.32,0:03:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,talk, you will have all the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.25,0:03:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,required information and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.41,0:03:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge that you need to make
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.07,0:03:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps work amazing in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple's ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.07,0:03:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's dig right in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.83,0:03:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with selecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.61,0:03:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When we talk about selecting, we
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.78,0:03:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,really want to answer the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.51,0:03:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,question, "What platform do I go
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.38,0:03:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.69,0:03:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you haven't launched your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.75,0:03:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,app yet, and you're trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.83,0:03:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,decide what your first platform
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.50,0:03:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, maybe, you have launched
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.06,0:03:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,your app on one or two
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.04,0:03:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms, and you're trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.27,0:03:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,decide where to go next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Two words come to mind that are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.50,0:03:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,really important when we talk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.98,0:03:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,about selecting a platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.12,0:03:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Context and capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.16,0:03:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Context is the time, the place,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.83,0:04:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the environment in which
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,your platform really comes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.45,0:04:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And, capabilities are the unique
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.26,0:04:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality that makes the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.90,0:04:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,platform distinct from all the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,other ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.32,0:04:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really important to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,understand context, as when
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.86,0:04:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,people switch context, they
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,often switch platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.79,0:04:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say that you're working
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,behind a desk at school or in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.27,0:04:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very focused and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.76,0:04:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,stationary context that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.25,0:04:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.91,0:04:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When you then leave that place,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.10,0:04:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and let's say you go to a bus or
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.12,0:04:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a train to head home, that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.52,0:04:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a very dynamic and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,mobile platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.92,0:04:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And, mobile context, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.32,0:04:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very big switch in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.61,0:04:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,context, from being very
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.59,0:04:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,stationary and focused to being
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.23,0:04:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,very mobile and public.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that also explains why
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.05,0:04:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,people would switch device.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.35,0:04:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They go from a MacBook or an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.96,0:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,iMac, to maybe a phone or Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.27,0:04:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that's because a phone and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.30,0:04:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a Watch is better optimized for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.23,0:04:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that context.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.27,0:04:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Understanding capabilities is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.62,0:04:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,equally important, as they
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,really allow you to see what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.87,0:04:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,makes a platform unique, and how
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.64,0:04:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,your app can benefit from that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:04:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.14,0:05:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you a few examples to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.70,0:05:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,show you what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with the iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.18,0:05:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the most familiar platform
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.77,0:05:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst all of us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.61,0:05:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the context of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.11,0:05:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the iPhone, it's always on, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.34,0:05:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,always with you, and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.66,0:05:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's mobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.50,0:05:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very personal and private
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.41,0:05:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.94,0:05:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't easily share it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.96,0:05:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with other people, and it's all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.95,0:05:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,optimized for quite short
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.16,0:05:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,engagements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.15,0:05:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Often when you use the iPhone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you maybe use it for a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes, not more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.62,0:05:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The capabilities support the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.94,0:05:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,context.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.20,0:05:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the phone is always on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.52,0:05:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and always with you, it's very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.04,0:05:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,environment aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a gyroscope, an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.26,0:05:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,accelerometer, and all that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.02,0:05:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,information is accessible with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.81,0:05:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,background processes even when
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.27,0:05:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not using the iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.63,0:05:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your phone is personal
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.92,0:05:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and private, it's protected with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.54,0:05:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Touch ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.90,0:05:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And, to make those short
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.61,0:05:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,engagements really easy and fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a very detailed touch
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.82,0:05:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.76,0:05:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watch is quite similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.88,0:05:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also always on and with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.94,0:05:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.60,0:05:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also personal and private,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's much more instant, and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.26,0:06:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,much more optimized for very
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.60,0:06:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,short interactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.29,0:06:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A Watch face, for example, gives
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.67,0:06:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you the right information just
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.28,0:06:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by looking at your Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.43,0:06:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And, notifications just show you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.86,0:06:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,more just by looking long
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.11,0:06:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.66,0:06:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The capabilities, again, support
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it, because the Watch is so
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.12,0:06:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,personal it can track your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.43,0:06:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,movement, it can track your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.65,0:06:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,heart, even your location.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.05,0:06:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The haptics can tell you when
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.12,0:06:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you should look at your Watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.64,0:06:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Watch faces allow you to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.96,0:06:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,customize the information you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.31,0:06:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,want to see at a glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.76,0:06:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the iPad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.82,0:06:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The iPad has a very mixed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.03,0:06:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,context.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.16,0:06:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use it both at home and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,on the go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do very precise and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.97,0:06:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,focused work on it, or just use
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it as a lean back device, for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.31,0:06:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,watching movies, TV shows, or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.26,0:06:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,playing games.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And, all of those are longer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.94,0:06:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,engagements than the phone or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.64,0:06:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.41,0:06:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The large screen really supports
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.69,0:06:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the context, because it allows
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you to do all that precise and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.01,0:06:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,focused work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.19,0:06:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The ambient light sensor allows
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.57,0:06:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you to use the iPad both in the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.71,0:07:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,evening and during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.96,0:07:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The high-fidelity speakers allow
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.09,0:07:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you to create a very immersive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.70,0:07:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,experience with games and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,movies, and you have that same
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.93,0:07:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,touch screen as on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.37,0:07:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And, if you add a pencil to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,well then it becomes a very
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.52,0:07:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,precise interaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.48,0:07:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the MacBook.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The context of the MacBook is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.58,0:07:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,always in a very professional
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.76,0:07:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do very precise and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,complex work on a MacBook which
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is why it's the preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,platform to design apps or to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.46,0:07:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,develop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.04,0:07:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be used as a shared
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.14,0:07:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,device, but it's always personal
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.06,0:07:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as everybody has their own
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.04,0:07:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,account.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.63,0:07:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you use the MacBook or the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,iMac for very long engagements.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.11,0:07:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of us here would probably
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.11,0:07:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,be using a MacBook or an iMac
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.28,0:07:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,several hours a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.15,0:07:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.32,0:07:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To do all that professional
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.21,0:07:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,work, it has a very high
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.84,0:07:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The keyboard and mouse allow you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.19,0:07:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to do very precise and complex
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.57,0:07:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.52,0:07:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Multitasking allows you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what you want to do, how
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.42,0:07:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.22,0:07:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And, multi users allow you to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.57,0:08:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,make the MacBook or the iMac a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.06,0:08:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,shared device, but still very
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.73,0:08:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, let's look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.09,0:08:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.59,0:08:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The Apple TV is a shared device.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.69,0:08:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You use it together with your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.56,0:08:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,family or your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.04,0:08:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stationary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.98,0:08:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You lock it to your TV and it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.29,0:08:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really move from that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.32,0:08:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,location.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.59,0:08:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And, it's completely optimized
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.84,0:08:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for a lean back experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.45,0:08:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can Watch movies, TV shows,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.18,0:08:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or play games.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.49,0:08:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And, again, all of those are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.38,0:08:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,longer engagements, often 30
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes, to maybe a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.54,0:08:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It works really well with an HD
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,display to make the content
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.21,0:08:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,really come alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.74,0:08:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The remote control is light and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.12,0:08:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,easy, and you can just pass it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.29,0:08:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,around to your friends and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.13,0:08:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's stationary it's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,very home aware, which is why it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.15,0:08:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,works so well with HomeKit, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.11,0:08:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's completely optimized for a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.48,0:08:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,10-foot distance, so you can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.97,0:08:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,really just sit back on the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.93,0:08:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,couch, relax, and enjoy the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.56,0:08:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see that understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the context and the capabilities
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.16,0:08:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of each platform is really
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.56,0:08:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,important to help you choose
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what platform to go to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.31,0:08:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The context is where it comes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.42,0:09:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,alive, and the capabilities is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.62,0:09:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what makes it unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.59,0:09:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And, the same goes for your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.24,0:09:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so you might want to ask
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.08,0:09:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself, in what context does
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.07,0:09:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,my app really come alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.19,0:09:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And, what are the capabilities
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.39,0:09:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it requires to do so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, we have a simple
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.03,0:09:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,exercise we like to do a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.47,0:09:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of times when we're trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.59,0:09:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,choose on which platforms an app
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.49,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,should be available on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.23,0:09:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And, I'll give you a few
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,examples to show you what I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.88,0:09:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.98,0:09:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at Activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.73,0:09:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think about the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics of Activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.37,0:09:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it has to be mobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.88,0:09:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Activity tracks your data --
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.42,0:09:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,tracks your movement the whole
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,day, so to give you accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.39,0:09:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,data, it has to be always on,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.02,0:09:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,always with you, and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,mobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.18,0:09:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It also has to be personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.95,0:09:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be able to track your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.10,0:09:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,data and only your data.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.82,0:09:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you look at these two
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.85,0:09:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics, what we do, is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.61,0:09:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we map them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.50,0:09:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to put them on a scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.61,0:09:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if we look at
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.66,0:09:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,mobile, we can map that out on a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.78,0:09:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,scale from mobile to stationary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.88,0:09:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look all of your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:10:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms on this scale, they
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.47,0:10:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,would lay out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watch is the most mobile
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,platform we have, the TV as we
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,said before, is the most
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.21,0:10:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,stationary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.94,0:10:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the other
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.90,0:10:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic, personal, we can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.99,0:10:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,map it out on a scale from
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.30,0:10:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,personal to shared, and we get
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.94,0:10:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watch is the most personal
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.23,0:10:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and mobile platform we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.08,0:10:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The TV is the most stationary
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.71,0:10:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.70,0:10:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When we looked at Activity, we
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.03,0:10:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,said, well it had to be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.98,0:10:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,personal, and it had to be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.65,0:10:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,mobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.11,0:10:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So on this chart, it's probably
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,located somewhere here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.41,0:10:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that explains why Activity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.74,0:10:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is available on these platforms,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.11,0:10:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and not on any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.09,0:10:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you another example,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.03,0:10:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,let's look at GarageBand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.87,0:10:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The characteristics of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.64,0:10:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,GarageBand is that you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.93,0:10:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to be really precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.26,0:10:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,manipulate sound exactly where
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.14,0:10:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.46,0:10:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And, secondly, it has to work
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.27,0:10:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with multitasking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:10:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be able to play
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.91,0:11:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple sounds at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.89,0:11:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it needs to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.72,0:11:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,handle all the hardware and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.99,0:11:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,instruments that you might
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.31,0:11:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,attach to the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.65,0:11:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again, we can map this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.86,0:11:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.70,0:11:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We can map that out on a scale
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.66,0:11:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from loose interactions to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.13,0:11:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,precise interactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.12,0:11:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The platforms lay out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.21,0:11:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,On a MacBook with a keyboard and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.55,0:11:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a mouse, you can be really
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.06,0:11:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,precise, but on a Watch, it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.58,0:11:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,very small screen and as
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.09,0:11:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody has fat fingers, you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.80,0:11:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,might not be able to be that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.83,0:11:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.42,0:11:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the other scale
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.53,0:11:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of multitasking, we can map that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.46,0:11:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,out on the scale from
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.28,0:11:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,multitasking to a single task.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,On a MacBook, you can easily do
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.26,0:11:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple tasks at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,On a Watch, you can only do one
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,single task at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at GarageBand to be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.25,0:11:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,set, it had to support
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.37,0:11:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,multitasking and it had to be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.30,0:11:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,very precise, so it's located
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.45,0:11:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere here, and that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.05,0:11:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,explains why it's available on
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.45,0:11:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,these three platforms, and not
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.82,0:11:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.47,0:11:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a very simple
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.00,0:12:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,example, two simple examples
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,actually of using these
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics to choose your
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.17,0:12:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.06,0:12:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this exercise over and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.58,0:12:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,over again with tons of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.80,0:12:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics, and in the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.59,0:12:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we hope that we can find a few
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.34,0:12:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms on which your app can
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.86,0:12:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,really come alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.41,0:12:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's exactly what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.64,0:12:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,selecting is all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.55,0:12:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is choosing a platform based
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,on the context it supports, and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.87,0:12:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the capabilities it provides,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's validating where your
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,app can benefit the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.45,0:12:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was step one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.90,0:12:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We looked at what platform we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.42,0:12:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to go to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're going to go and look
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.01,0:12:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at adapting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.67,0:12:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With adapting, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.44,0:12:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,look at all the interactions,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.80,0:12:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,all the features, all the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.21,0:12:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality we want to bring
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.40,0:12:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to our app, and try to manage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.10,0:12:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that across the platforms that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to be available on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.97,0:12:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll explain, again with an
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.14,0:12:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,example.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.06,0:12:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at Activity on the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.00,0:12:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.14,0:12:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Activity on the iPhone, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.31,0:12:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,do a whole range of features.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:12:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at your progress of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:13:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,today, you can look at your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.19,0:13:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,achievements, your workouts, you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can see how your friends are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.32,0:13:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.32,0:13:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you can manage all that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.26,0:13:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,data.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.69,0:13:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can add workouts, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.12,0:13:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,invite friends, you can share
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.02,0:13:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the achievements, you can share
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.64,0:13:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.77,0:13:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All of that is possible on the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.19,0:13:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone, and that works well if
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.17,0:13:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you think back about the context
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.64,0:13:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.31,0:13:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The iPhone was a very personal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.53,0:13:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,device, and all these
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.83,0:13:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,interactions that you're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.85,0:13:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is with personal information,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.19,0:13:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and the iPhone was optimized for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.43,0:13:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,quite short engagements.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.99,0:13:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And, all of these interactions,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.34,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't take very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.27,0:13:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do them relatively
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.35,0:13:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.61,0:13:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you look at how that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.99,0:13:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,scales to the Watch, we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.55,0:13:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the feature set is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.47,0:13:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,greatly reduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.43,0:13:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And, again, this makes sense if
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.72,0:13:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you think back about the context
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.27,0:13:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.55,0:13:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watch is still a very
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.44,0:13:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,personal device, and all these
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.12,0:13:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,interactions, all this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.99,0:13:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,information is still very
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.08,0:13:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,personal, but as we said, the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.86,0:13:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch is optimized for really
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.47,0:13:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,short interactions, glances
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.08,0:13:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.39,0:13:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we made sure that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.39,0:13:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,look at your own progress at a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.90,0:13:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,glance, and you can see how your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:13:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,friends are doing at a glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.40,0:14:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one really big part about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.53,0:14:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,adapting is seeing how you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,manage your interactions, your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.41,0:14:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality across all the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms that you want to be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.00,0:14:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,available on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.11,0:14:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Another part, is looking at what
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.07,0:14:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,unique capabilities a platform
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.03,0:14:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,can provide, and how your app
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.84,0:14:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,can benefit from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.91,0:14:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When we looked at the Watch, we
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,said, well, some of the unique
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.45,0:14:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities of the Watch is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.40,0:14:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that it can track your movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.59,0:14:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it can track your heartbeat,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.11,0:14:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your location, and all of that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.98,0:14:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,information is quite relevant
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.45,0:14:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for an app like Activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.57,0:14:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you look at what
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.76,0:14:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,additional features we brought
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.13,0:14:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Watch, well, you can add
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.75,0:14:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a workout, and you can set move
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.49,0:14:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.34,0:14:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And, again, this only makes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.90,0:14:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sense if you look at the context
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.20,0:14:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and the capabilities of the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.66,0:14:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.97,0:14:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's exactly what adapting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.49,0:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.44,0:14:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is prioritizing your feature,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,your features based on the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.41,0:14:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,platform's context and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.38,0:14:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities, and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.11,0:14:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,considering new features that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.42,0:14:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,can benefit from the platform's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,unique capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:15:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A really good example of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.43,0:15:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is Photoshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.46,0:15:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,For those of you who've used
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.57,0:15:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Photoshop on a MacBook or an
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.86,0:15:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,iMac, you know that it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.38,0:15:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,really enormous, big app.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.67,0:15:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's tons of features in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.11,0:15:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do so many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.43,0:15:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Adobe did a really good job
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.10,0:15:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when they tried to bring all
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.11,0:15:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,those features to the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.05,0:15:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually broke down the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.19,0:15:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,feature set into 3 really
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.23,0:15:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,distinct apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.66,0:15:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the interactions are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,optimized for quite short
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.81,0:15:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,engagements, and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.51,0:15:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,embracing the unique
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.38,0:15:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities of a phone by, for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,example, being able to take a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,picture right from within the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.77,0:15:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.30,0:15:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Another good example is the New
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.51,0:15:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,York Times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to read an article
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.02,0:15:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the New York Times, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.27,0:15:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,do that on the phone, on the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.74,0:15:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad, or on their website.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you look at what they've
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,done on the Watch, you can only
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,look through a series of the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,most recent headlines, and if
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.23,0:15:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you're interested in one of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.08,0:15:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,them, you can flick down and you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.51,0:15:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,can see a small summary of that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,article, but if you want to read
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.85,0:15:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the full article, well that's a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:15:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,longer engagement, so it's no
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:15:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,longer optimized for the Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.76,0:15:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And, therefore, they ask you to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.09,0:16:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,go to the iPhone, the iPad, or
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.87,0:16:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the website.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.91,0:16:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was adapting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In step one, we looked at what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms you wanted to go to,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.06,0:16:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and step two we looked at the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,features, and now we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the look and feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.91,0:16:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When people talk about look and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.09,0:16:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,feel, they often think about the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.31,0:16:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,word consistent, and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.31,0:16:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,definitely a very important word
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.52,0:16:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.54,0:16:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,bringing your app to multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.70,0:16:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But, consistent doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.81,0:16:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.13,0:16:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, we don't just copy and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.62,0:16:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,paste all functionality and all
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.32,0:16:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the visual elements from one
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.54,0:16:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,platform to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.44,0:16:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Being consistent is much more of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.04,0:16:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a balancing act.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.73,0:16:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to balance between two
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.58,0:16:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,types of consistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.97,0:16:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,On one side, you have your brand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.30,0:16:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,consistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.71,0:16:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that when people open
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.11,0:16:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,your app, they should recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.77,0:16:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,your brand, it should feel very
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.47,0:16:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar, and hopefully that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.08,0:16:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,will build trust between the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,person who's using your app, and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.26,0:16:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your brand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.26,0:16:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side, you have the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.42,0:16:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,platform guidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This means you'd be using
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.44,0:17:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,platform-provided standards, so
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.05,0:17:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your app feels native.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.31,0:17:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Since these standards reoccur on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.83,0:17:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,all the apps on that platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.51,0:17:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they will feel very
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That lowers the cognitive load,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.45,0:17:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and that eases the learning
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.37,0:17:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.89,0:17:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, finding the balance between
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.06,0:17:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,these two types of consistencies
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.87,0:17:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is really important, and maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.57,0:17:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the most difficult exercise in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this whole process.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.80,0:17:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The human interface guidelines
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.98,0:17:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,can be a really good help here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.83,0:17:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They can help you understand all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.21,0:17:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the platform-provided standards
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and guidelines, but it can also
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.35,0:17:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,help you understand where your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.03,0:17:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,brand can really come alive
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.58,0:17:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,within these guidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.09,0:17:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,One example is the typefaces we
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.96,0:17:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that for each platform
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.14,0:17:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a nice set of typefaces
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.64,0:17:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can use, and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.01,0:17:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,all optimized for the platform
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.28,0:17:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they're on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.71,0:17:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't mean that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.80,0:17:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to use San Francisco, or you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.05,0:17:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,have to use this specific
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.16,0:17:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,typeface or style, but it gives
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.70,0:17:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you a really good idea on what
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.11,0:17:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes work well for each
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.56,0:18:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take a look at the body
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.11,0:18:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,style for example, on these
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,three platforms, you'll see that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.41,0:18:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they nicely scale up, and that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.38,0:18:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with the viewing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.36,0:18:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.04,0:18:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,On a Watch, you look at a Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.11,0:18:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,from quite close, maybe a foot
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,away, so it's quite small.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.39,0:18:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A phone is a little bit further
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.61,0:18:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe one and a half foot, so
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.18,0:18:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a tiny bit bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.48,0:18:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But on a TV as we said before,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it was optimized for a 10-foot
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,distance, so we made it really
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.28,0:18:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,big so you can read it from that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.19,0:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,distance quite comfortably.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.01,0:18:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Apart from the stylistic
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.53,0:18:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,features, the human interface
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.61,0:18:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines can also help you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.20,0:18:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with platform-provided standards
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.51,0:18:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and functionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.94,0:18:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, alerts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.00,0:18:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Alerts come on every single
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.63,0:18:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,platform that we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.92,0:18:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And, they have some common
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.95,0:18:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.07,0:18:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a description, they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.65,0:18:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,have one or two actions, they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.62,0:18:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,obscure the content behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.65,0:18:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you look at the length
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.25,0:18:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the description, the styling
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.64,0:18:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of the buttons, the tap targets,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.96,0:18:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all optimized for each
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:18:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.40,0:18:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, using an alert like this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.67,0:19:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,will make the -- will be very
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.29,0:19:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar to the user,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizable, and therefore easy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.82,0:19:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The same goes for navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.22,0:19:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If I want to navigate to the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.73,0:19:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,previous screen on my Watch, I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.01,0:19:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,can just tap the top left
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.16,0:19:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.00,0:19:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The same happens on the iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.95,0:19:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you look at a TV, well
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no back button on the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.86,0:19:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.95,0:19:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that's because the back
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.05,0:19:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,button is actually located on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.53,0:19:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your remote.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's no need to add an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,extra button on the screen to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.51,0:19:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,navigate to, and to click.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.34,0:19:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's exactly what
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.47,0:19:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,conforming is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finding the balance between
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.15,0:19:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,your brand and the platform
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.52,0:19:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.96,0:19:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's aligning with your brand,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.06,0:19:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so your brand feels
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizable, familiar, and can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.85,0:19:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,create trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.81,0:19:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And, it's aligning with the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.64,0:19:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,platform guidelines and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.55,0:19:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality to lower the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.12,0:19:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,cognitive load and to ease the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.17,0:19:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,learning curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.37,0:19:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A really good example is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.38,0:20:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ulysses, and I really hope I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,pronouncing that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.43,0:20:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If not, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you use this app on the iPad,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the iPhone, or the Mac, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.25,0:20:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,notice a whole bunch of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.35,0:20:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,platform-provided standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.00,0:20:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They're using navigation bars,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.53,0:20:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,toolbars, search fields, and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.82,0:20:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,split views.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.87,0:20:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And, where their brand is really
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.12,0:20:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,represented is in the writing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.62,0:20:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.07,0:20:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,By allowing dedicated focus, and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.99,0:20:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,quick formatting with markdown,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,writing becomes an amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.08,0:20:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,experience in this app.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.26,0:20:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I use this app very frequently
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.99,0:20:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in my process, and in fact, this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.28,0:20:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation started in this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.31,0:20:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.66,0:20:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Another good example is Streaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.07,0:20:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With Streaks, you immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.03,0:20:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize the brand through the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.29,0:20:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,color, the typography, the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.04,0:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,iconography, even the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction of long-holding to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.94,0:20:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,complete a task.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But, they really embraced the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.74,0:20:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,platform guidelines with, for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.25,0:20:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,example, doing very smart
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.49,0:20:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications, scaling the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.33,0:20:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,typography, and adapting to new
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.58,0:20:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.64,0:20:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And a last good example, is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.22,0:20:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.25,0:20:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, you would recognize the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.41,0:21:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,iconography, you recognize the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,colors, the interaction of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.62,0:21:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,swiping left and right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.50,0:21:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But, again, they really aligned
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.02,0:21:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with the platform guidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.66,0:21:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The UI scales up very nicely to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.44,0:21:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the different platforms, and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.14,0:21:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,their unique interaction of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.22,0:21:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,swiping left and right never
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.76,0:21:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,interferes with platform
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.94,0:21:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.52,0:21:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, that was step three.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.41,0:21:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if this is the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.54,0:21:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to launch your app
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.35,0:21:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,on your first platform, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.02,0:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.01,0:21:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You selected your platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.71,0:21:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you've defined your features,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you've defined your look and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.08,0:21:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.23,0:21:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you can start building it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.20,0:21:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopefully launch it on the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.21,0:21:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,App Store.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.59,0:21:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if this is an app that you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.72,0:21:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,want to launch on your second,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.21,0:21:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,third, or next platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.47,0:21:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,connecting becomes a really
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.74,0:21:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,important step.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.23,0:21:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When we talk about connecting,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.54,0:21:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,two points in your experience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.10,0:21:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,are really important.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.88,0:21:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the entry point and the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,exit point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.28,0:21:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The entry point is when you open
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.56,0:21:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the app, and you start using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.63,0:21:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The exit point is, hopefully
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.12,0:22:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,after a while, when you've done
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.26,0:22:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,some work in the app, you close
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.27,0:22:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it and you go do something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.59,0:22:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These two points are really
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.82,0:22:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,important, even when you're just
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.16,0:22:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,using one platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.37,0:22:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time you open the app
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.76,0:22:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,again, you hope it doesn't just
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.36,0:22:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,give you that same opening
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.74,0:22:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.95,0:22:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But, that it actually helps you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.19,0:22:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,create the same environment you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.49,0:22:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,were in the last time you had
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.15,0:22:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the app open.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.81,0:22:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what we call recreating
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.49,0:22:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,state.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.52,0:22:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And, by state, we mean the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.60,0:22:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,content and the information, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.49,0:22:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the settings that you were using
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.72,0:22:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the last time you had the app
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.04,0:22:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,open.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.66,0:22:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The state can take any shape or
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.12,0:22:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,form depending on what your app
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.48,0:22:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,does.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.61,0:22:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For a simple app like Weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.86,0:22:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for example, it should at least
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.70,0:22:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,open up on the same location or
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.42,0:22:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,city that you were looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.50,0:22:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the last time you had the app
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.54,0:22:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,open.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.48,0:22:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Preferably with the weather
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.80,0:22:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,information updated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.11,0:22:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For a more complex app like
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.40,0:22:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Notes, it would open the same
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.18,0:22:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,note you were working in last
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.36,0:22:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,time, if possible, with the same
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.48,0:22:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,tools selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.99,0:22:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And, for apps that revolve
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.49,0:23:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,around media for example, like
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.22,0:23:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,games, movies, or TV shows, you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.30,0:23:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,would hope it would resume where
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.81,0:23:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you last left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.23,0:23:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, in the game you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.38,0:23:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't have to play that game
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.46,0:23:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,all over again just to get to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.64,0:23:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that same point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.09,0:23:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Remembering state becomes even
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.44,0:23:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,more important when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.33,0:23:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,switching between platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.22,0:23:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Being able to remember and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.09,0:23:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,recreate the last used state on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.89,0:23:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,any platform creates a very
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.99,0:23:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,effortless and delightful
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.65,0:23:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.21,0:23:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It allows people to enjoy your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.42,0:23:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,app in whichever context they
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.84,0:23:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,like, because you as an app
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.23,0:23:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,developer and designer, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.07,0:23:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,take care of optimizing that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.32,0:23:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,experience for the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.52,0:23:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, we really try to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.10,0:23:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,embrace connecting platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.31,0:23:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in TV, the state
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.55,0:23:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the TV app remembers is where
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.92,0:23:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you last stopped watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The TV show you were watching
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.49,0:23:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the time you paused is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.88,0:23:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,synced across all the devices,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.62,0:23:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can resume on any
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.79,0:23:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,platform of your choosing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.63,0:23:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Another good example is Maps.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.44,0:24:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning I looked up on my
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.05,0:24:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,MacBook how to get to this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.48,0:24:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,convention center.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.89,0:24:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I did that, that search
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.63,0:24:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,went into my recent searches.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.59,0:24:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And, recent searches is a state
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.30,0:24:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that's being recreated on all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.42,0:24:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.87,0:24:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I step into my car, that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.32,0:24:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,recent search popped up in the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.41,0:24:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,list, I can just tap it and get
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.06,0:24:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,going.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.17,0:24:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This all works really well if
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.70,0:24:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you have your apps set up on all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.06,0:24:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your platforms, and you're good
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.19,0:24:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.52,0:24:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happens when a new
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.88,0:24:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,platform comes in?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.77,0:24:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say that you're using a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.74,0:24:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,MacBook and a phone, and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.66,0:24:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you buy an iPad, and it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.10,0:24:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a part of your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.97,0:24:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,day-to-day life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.91,0:24:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you install the app on the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.07,0:24:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad, and most of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.59,0:24:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,before the app can actually
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.53,0:24:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,recreate the state you were in,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.02,0:24:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it needs a bit more information.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.09,0:24:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an additional step
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.07,0:24:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that's required, which is a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.07,0:24:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,set-up step.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.85,0:24:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The app needs to know who you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.97,0:24:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are, so it can recreate the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.22,0:24:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,state you were in, the last time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.70,0:24:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you had the app open on another
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.25,0:24:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.52,0:24:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And, often, such a set-up step
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.46,0:24:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,looks something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.18,0:24:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And, this can be quite
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.24,0:24:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,off-putting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.63,0:25:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to remember your email
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.52,0:25:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,address, your user name, your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.69,0:25:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,password, you have to type it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.36,0:25:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in, you might type it in wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.43,0:25:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, it might be so
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.48,0:25:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,off-putting that you actually
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.08,0:25:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,skip this and you don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.03,0:25:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,use this app on your new
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.00,0:25:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.39,0:25:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But, luckily with features like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.81,0:25:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,iCloud Keychain, you can just
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.76,0:25:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,make this step really effortless
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.04,0:25:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.90,0:25:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,With the tap of a button, iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.49,0:25:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Keychain can fill in your user
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.98,0:25:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,name, your email, and your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.63,0:25:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,password, and you're just good
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.19,0:25:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.22,0:25:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, we really embrace this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.32,0:25:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,part as well, this set-up step,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.83,0:25:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,especially with new platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.65,0:25:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you buy an Apple TV, you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.06,0:25:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to set it up
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.84,0:25:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,manually, you can just hold your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.17,0:25:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone or your iPad close to the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.52,0:25:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV, and it will move over
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.71,0:25:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all the apps that are compatible
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.00,0:25:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with Apple TV as well as your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.96,0:25:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,iTunes store credentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.51,0:25:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the Apple TV has done
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.86,0:25:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,setting up, you will recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.23,0:25:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,all the apps that are on there,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.46,0:25:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because you also have them on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.33,0:25:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,your phone, and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.74,0:25:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately start buying TV
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.07,0:25:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,shows, movies, or games, because
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.45,0:25:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the iTunes store credentials are
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.44,0:25:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.73,0:26:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those are really good
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.62,0:26:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,examples of connecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.27,0:26:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Connecting is creating a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.44,0:26:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous experience between
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.76,0:26:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms, by remembering the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.48,0:26:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,state, and optimizing for the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.86,0:26:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,entry and exit point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.07,0:26:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And, it's allowing for a quick
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.26,0:26:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and easy way to use this new
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.88,0:26:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.89,0:26:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A really good example is Things.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.22,0:26:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The state that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.94,0:26:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,recreating is your to-do list.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.23,0:26:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,On any platform that you access
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Things on, you can add a to-do
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.89,0:26:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,item, you can mark one as done,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.37,0:26:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you can add a due date or
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.74,0:26:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,organize it, and it will just
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.54,0:26:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sync that information across all
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.85,0:26:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,your devices simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.97,0:26:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Deliveries does a very similar
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.17,0:26:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.43,0:26:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It remembers a list of tracking
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.31,0:26:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers that you've saved in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.53,0:26:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,iCloud, and it will update the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.40,0:26:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,information from the delivery
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.96,0:26:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,service for each single item.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.44,0:26:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that information is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.34,0:26:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible on any platform you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.01,0:26:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,open it up on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.25,0:26:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And, a really good example of a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.49,0:26:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,seamless login experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.00,0:26:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Instagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.30,0:27:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you install Instagram, and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.57,0:27:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you have Facebook installed, it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.59,0:27:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will just use those credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.17,0:27:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to get you logged in to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.21,0:27:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Instagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.06,0:27:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with a simple tap of a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.06,0:27:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,button, Instagram is opened up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.89,0:27:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for you, and you're good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.46,0:27:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was connecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.30,0:27:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We looked at what happens when
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.72,0:27:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you go from one platform to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.91,0:27:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,another.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.20,0:27:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In step five, we actually look
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.15,0:27:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at what happens when two
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.35,0:27:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms are available at the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.38,0:27:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.71,0:27:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And, to do that, I'm going to go
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.85,0:27:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,back to what we talked about in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.24,0:27:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,step one, in selecting, to the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.34,0:27:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,context and the capabilities of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.91,0:27:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.39,0:27:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the MacBook again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.21,0:27:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, well, it had a very
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.47,0:27:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,high performance, you could do
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.07,0:27:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,really precise work with the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.12,0:27:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard and mouse, it could do
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.51,0:27:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,multitasking, but maybe what
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.46,0:27:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not really good at, is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.89,0:27:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly knowing who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.56,0:27:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, when I open up my
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.21,0:27:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,MacBook from sleep or I start it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.14,0:27:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,up from when it's off, I get
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.95,0:27:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.43,0:27:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to type in my password or
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.96,0:28:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to give my Touch ID to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.39,0:28:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,login.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.67,0:28:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And, again, just like the login
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.08,0:28:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,experience before, if I need to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.83,0:28:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,type in my password, that could
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.50,0:28:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,be quite off-putting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.06,0:28:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to remember it, I might
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.35,0:28:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,type it wrong, it could take a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.05,0:28:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.57,0:28:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But, this is the only way for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.84,0:28:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the MacBook to know who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.77,0:28:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's really no other way for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.84,0:28:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it to verify my identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.92,0:28:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you bring in a Watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.91,0:28:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,well, a Watch is always on and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.18,0:28:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,always with you, and it actually
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.86,0:28:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,knows who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.57,0:28:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when these two start talking
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.97,0:28:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to each other, really magical
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.79,0:28:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,things can happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.71,0:28:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watch can tell you -- can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.23,0:28:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,tell the MacBook, that this is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.53,0:28:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,actually you, and login for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.03,0:28:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and before you know it, your
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.89,0:28:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,MacBook just opens up for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.67,0:28:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's really important to note
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.73,0:28:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,here, is how effortless this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.48,0:28:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,experience is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.81,0:28:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to tell my MacBook
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.11,0:28:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen to my Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.88,0:28:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to tell the Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.04,0:28:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to give information to the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.99,0:28:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,MacBook.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.94,0:28:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It just happens because they're
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.07,0:28:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,close.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.11,0:28:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I don't have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.23,0:28:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.52,0:28:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, making an experience
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.48,0:28:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,effortless when you have
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.66,0:29:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple platforms available, is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.55,0:29:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,really important.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.73,0:29:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Adding a platform should not
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.94,0:29:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,result in adding additional
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.31,0:29:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.56,0:29:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at another platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.63,0:29:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,let's look at the iMac.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.59,0:29:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said before, iMac, high
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.29,0:29:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,performance, big display, really
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.75,0:29:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,good for, for example, browsing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.97,0:29:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the internet, and maybe even
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.00,0:29:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.67,0:29:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What the iMac cannot do,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.78,0:29:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,unfortunately, is store your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.55,0:29:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,ApplePay card securely.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.52,0:29:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is why you can't do that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.81,0:29:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on an iMac at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.69,0:29:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But an iPhone can.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.49,0:29:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So when these two start talking
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.68,0:29:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to each other, suddenly payments
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.56,0:29:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.78,0:29:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When you want to buy something
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.60,0:29:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on the iMac, it will tell you to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.20,0:29:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,go to your phone, your phone
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.76,0:29:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,will use your securely stored
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.13,0:29:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,ApplePay cards, with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.20,0:29:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,authentication with Touch ID,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.34,0:29:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you confirm the payment, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.26,0:29:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you're good to go, the payment
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.19,0:29:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is complete, and you can keep
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.78,0:29:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.27,0:29:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And, this doesn't have to be on
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.40,0:29:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,an iPhone, this works on an
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.73,0:29:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad, or on a Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.69,0:29:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's really important here to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.96,0:29:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,note, is how clear the control
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.92,0:29:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.91,0:30:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The iMac is clearly telling me
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.57,0:30:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.09,0:30:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,On my phone, I get a nice
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.18,0:30:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,summary of what I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.51,0:30:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,purchase.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.33,0:30:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,With Touch ID, I confirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.94,0:30:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The same happens on the Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.96,0:30:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with double click to confirm,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.73,0:30:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and before I know it, my
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.15,0:30:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,purchase is complete, and I can
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.43,0:30:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,continue my experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.43,0:30:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, giving really clear control
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.23,0:30:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is incredibly important when
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.57,0:30:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple platforms become
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.86,0:30:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,available.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.27,0:30:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, your experience might
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.55,0:30:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,become very complicated and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.23,0:30:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.17,0:30:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And, lastly, let's look at
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.81,0:30:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Keynote.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.24,0:30:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Keynote is a fantastic app to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.66,0:30:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,make presentations, and also to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.23,0:30:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,give them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.93,0:30:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But, one of the downsides of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.91,0:30:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,giving a presentation is that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.08,0:30:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,often, your MacBook is connected
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.51,0:30:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to a display or a projector.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.15,0:30:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And, so if you want to move
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.60,0:30:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,between the slides, you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.81,0:30:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,stay behind your MacBook because
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.07,0:30:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the keyboard is the only way to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.72,0:30:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,move between slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.48,0:30:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you bring in a phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.76,0:30:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,well then, the phone can take
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.87,0:30:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,control of what slide is being
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.67,0:30:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,shown, and you can freely move
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.33,0:31:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,around, because the phone is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.39,0:31:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,light, and easy to carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.80,0:31:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important to note about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.86,0:31:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,this experience, is that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.94,0:31:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,all optional.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.36,0:31:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If my phone runs out of battery,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.70,0:31:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or I forget it, I can still go
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.49,0:31:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,back to my MacBook, and use the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.08,0:31:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard to move between the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.21,0:31:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.07,0:31:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, making it optional is really
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.79,0:31:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,important for multiple devices
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.74,0:31:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in one experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.25,0:31:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's what extending is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.32,0:31:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.55,0:31:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We complement different
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.57,0:31:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms by combining their
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.96,0:31:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.67,0:31:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We make clear how to control the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.73,0:31:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,different devices, and we work
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.61,0:31:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,toward an optional and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.79,0:31:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,effortless experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.21,0:31:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A really good example is Timber
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.34,0:31:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.41,0:31:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Games have always really well
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.68,0:31:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,understood how multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.14,0:31:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms can really create a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.31,0:31:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,magical experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.17,0:31:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great example.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.48,0:31:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can play a multiplayer game
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.88,0:31:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with multiple devices if you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.11,0:31:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.22,0:31:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.69,0:31:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With a simple tap of a button,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.03,0:31:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can start a multiplayer
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.04,0:31:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.11,0:31:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's very clear control,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.73,0:31:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's only two buttons
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.11,0:31:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on the screen, and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.97,0:32:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,completely optional.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.89,0:32:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can play with a TV, an
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.83,0:32:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone, or an iPad, or any
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.84,0:32:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,combination of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.81,0:32:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And another good example is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.77,0:32:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Zova.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.41,0:32:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Zova works really well even if
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.95,0:32:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you only have one device.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.59,0:32:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have an iPad, or an
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.24,0:32:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone, or an Apple TV, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.10,0:32:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,start training with Zova, but
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.26,0:32:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the app will always look if
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.52,0:32:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,there are more platforms
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.53,0:32:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,available in its surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.61,0:32:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.34,0:32:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch, it will measure your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.82,0:32:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,heartbeat, and that information
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.40,0:32:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is shared amongst all the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.50,0:32:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,devices that you are using.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.00,0:32:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, that would
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.86,0:32:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,reappear on your TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.67,0:32:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great example of how
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.79,0:32:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,effortless this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.85,0:32:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, you don't have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.83,0:32:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,anything to make this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.69,0:32:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,information being shared across
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.07,0:32:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.43,0:32:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to tell my Watch to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.30,0:32:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,show my heartbeat on the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.01,0:32:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And, it's completely optional.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.53,0:32:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Zova works just as well with one
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.08,0:32:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,platform as it does with
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.51,0:32:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.05,0:32:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the entire process.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.34,0:33:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We started with selecting our
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.55,0:33:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,platform based on the context
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.09,0:33:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the capabilities of each
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.75,0:33:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.14,0:33:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We looked at prioritizing new
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.62,0:33:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and existing features, and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.74,0:33:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,taking advantage of unique
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.03,0:33:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities with adapting.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.20,0:33:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With conform, we tried to find a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.54,0:33:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,balance between our brand and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.06,0:33:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the platform guidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.39,0:33:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In connecting, we looked at what
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.65,0:33:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,happens when you go from one
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.86,0:33:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,platform to another, and make
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.72,0:33:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that really seamless and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.59,0:33:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.00,0:33:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And, lastly, we looked at what
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.56,0:33:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,magical things can happen when
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.18,0:33:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple devices are available
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.22,0:33:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.56,0:33:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I said in the beginning, we
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.08,0:33:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,design our platforms and our
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.16,0:33:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,apps to benefit your day-to-day
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.63,0:33:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,life, and create a meaningful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.27,0:33:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.71,0:33:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, we hope that all of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.36,0:33:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,our apps and platforms create a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.98,0:33:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,holistic experience that is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.40,0:33:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,greater than its parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.92,0:33:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,With this process we talked
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.97,0:33:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about today, we hope you have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.42,0:33:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all the tools you need to join
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.88,0:33:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,us in that endeavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.37,0:33:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This talk is always available
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.64,0:33:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,with this link, and make sure to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.99,0:34:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,check out these sessions too.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.50,0:34:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some really good ones
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.46,0:34:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow on design as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.94,0:34:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We wish you the best of luck in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.02,0:34:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,bringing your apps to Apple's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.30,0:34:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.26,0:34:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy the rest of WWDC, and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.37,0:34:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much.
